ds on what we understand by the term spirituality. Many have this notion th=
at spirituality only means sitting and doing tough penances ETC. There is m=
ore to spirituality than that. Essentially, it is a transformation of mind,=
 emotions and body (this bit is nearly impossible) into another state. 

Sa=
dhana is needed to prepare the ground - mind/emotions/body. But *meeting Go=
d* (as you put it) depends on what you mean by God, and on God's sweet will=
. Sometimes, living your daily life with an internal sense of surrender to =
a Supreme, trying to inculcate equanimity in testing circumstances, trying =
to stop the mind from automatically reacting to provocations, seeing other =
people's point of views and thus becoming more objective, trying to be comp=
assionate (but not self-pity or pity in any form, for pity is a degenerativ=
e emotion, while compassion is uplifting) ETC are all sadhanas which can be=
 done by anybody. One need not read complex scriptures, or believe in relig=
ion to be able to do these. 

